								<div class="title" id="post-title-4554319">
																		A Critique
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/marcelles-raynes" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5722579); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5722579&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251212" alt="Marcelles_Raynes" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5722579)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/marcelles-raynes" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5722579); return false;" >Marcelles_Raynes</a></span> <span class="odate time_1584570417 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Mar 2020 22:26</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4554319">
									

<p>Crit is somewhat out of order so be wary. I enjoyed the beginning quite a lot! +1 from me!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">[+]&nbsp;Reveal&nbsp;a&nbsp;madman's&nbsp;thoughts&nbsp;[+]</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;[-]&nbsp;Return&nbsp;to&nbsp;the&nbsp;darkness&nbsp;[-]</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Overall, let me just say that I really enjoy this piece. I think that this serves as an excellent way to introduce new readers to the Foundation and as a good in-universe execution of an orientation.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This is a basic amnestic inhalant. Take it, and we fix your little fishbowl and you can go back to living in it. Or you don’t. That’s the other option. Remember it all. Maybe you’re sick of the fishbowl.&nbsp;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I especially liked the red pill, blue pill scenario toward the end. If you drew inspiration from the Matrix (which is where my mind immediately went), then this is a neat little Easter egg. Correlatively I think this is a good analogy for what joining the Foundation is like. Maybe it would he better for some to live in ignorance of the anomalous, maybe some want to be red pulled and wake up. I think this is interesting.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>&nbsp;Welcome to the real world. In every shadow is a new unspeakable monstrosity. A new hexed object. In every crowd is a human with extraordinary and terrible powers. And on every block of every street is a new shadowy organization trying to control them and you.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is good but there are a few things here I don't like. I feel the use of the word &quot;In&quot; in the second line is unnecessary. (Welcome to the real world. Every shadow&#8230;). Also a common should be added here -》(every shadow is a new, unspeakable monstrosity.). The sentences surrounding &quot;A new hexed object&quot; seem flavorful, but that one sentence seems rather mundane by comparison. Also, just a thing I learned in college is to avoid using the same noun or verb twice per paragraph. (&quot;Every shadow&#8230; a new shadowy organization). For me, this breaks up the flow and takes the reader back into an earlier part of the paragraph.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“Don’t worry, we’re the good guys. And why am I saying that? Because we let you live this far. The others wouldn’t do that. You’re just gonna have to trust me on that.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;And why am I saying that?&quot; Seems unneeded. So, with my edit it should read &quot;&#8230;good guys. We let you live; the others wouldn't do that.&quot;. Also the final &quot;on that&quot; is not needed either.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“Who are we? We are called the SCP Foundation. That’s Special Containment Procedures. We do three things: secure, contain and protect. We secure the things that go bump in the night like chupacabra back there. We contain them so things like this don’t happen. And we do it to protect you. We’re a worldwide organization comprised of scientists and agents who have dedicated our lives to this cause.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Ah, this is nice. Just a minor thing here. &quot;We are the SCP Foundation&quot; instead of &quot;We are called the SCP Foundation.&quot; The way this is written implies that the Foundation was given the name by some force other than themselves. Structurally this is sound but I think it could better. &quot;We do three things: We secure the things that go bump in the night like chupacabra back there. We contain them so things like this don’t happen, and we do it to protect you. We’re a worldwide organization&#8230;&quot; this is what I would change this paragraph to.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

