								<div class="title" id="post-title-4554438">
																		My Thoughts
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/truc-linh" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5813515); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5813515&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251212" alt="Truc Linh" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5813515)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/truc-linh" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5813515); return false;" >Truc Linh</a></span> <span class="odate time_1584579260 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Mar 2020 00:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4554438">
									

<p>Reading this, I feel like the characters are reading off of a story or script rather than having more of a natural conversation (unless that one speaker is really extra). I am a bit mindful that this is a conversation, so of course it shouldn't be perfect since people in-universe make mistakes too, and given the circumstance they're in.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Here&nbsp;are&nbsp;my&nbsp;thoughts</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;More&nbsp;like&nbsp;crit...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>What actually happened was an&nbsp;eleven-foot tall mammal-like reptile&nbsp;you might call a “chupacabra”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like you could add &quot;, which&quot; between the &quot;reptile&quot; and the &quot;you&quot;, and maybe another comma after &quot;chupacabra&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>injected your neighbors and family with a powerful hemorrhagic poison, and then sucked up their insides</p>
</blockquote>
<p>For better flow, I suggest something like, &quot;injected a powerful hemorrhagic poison into your neighbors and family, then sucked up their insides&quot;<br />
That way, it sounds less awkward, and you won't have the &quot;, and&quot; without a subject.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>That’s Special Containment Procedures.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like this comes off as a bit awkward in the paragraph. How about &quot;That stands for Special Containment Procedures.&quot; instead?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We do three things: we secure the things that go bump in the night like chupacabra back there.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I feel like you could replace the second &quot;thing&quot; with &quot;anomalies&quot;, so you wouldn't have an awkward repeat of &quot;things&quot;. Additionally, I feel like the second &quot;we&quot; is also unnecessary because you've already previously mentioned it. I also think there could be a comma between &quot;night&quot; and &quot;like&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We contain them so things like this don’t happen.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>There should probably be a comma before &quot;so&quot; since it's a fanboy, and the sentences on both sides could stand on their own.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>You may not have looked into the void but it’s looked back at you.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>What you currently have is, &quot;&#8230; it is looked back at you&quot;. I would suggest, &quot;&#8230; into the void, but it had looked back at you&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>we fix your little fishbowl and you can go back to living in it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Comma between &quot;fishbowl&quot; and &quot;and&quot; since it's another fanboy.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Or you don’t. That’s the other option.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I think you could rephrase it as &quot;If you don't, that's the other option&quot;.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Not a single day is boring, though.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I personally don't see the comma as nessary, but yes, it's dialogue. Dialogue tends to be more wishy washy with grammar rules.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>“Yesterday I worked with&nbsp;a Tibetan monk who moves at 200 kilometers per hour&nbsp;all day.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Feel like this could be rephrased as &quot;All day yesterday, I worked with a Tibetan monk who moves at 200 kilometers per hour.<br /></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
I know that it doesn't need to look perfect for it to be natural&#8212;especially for dialogue, but I hope this is somewhat helpful with some of the grammar. Overall, it's okay to me, but I feel like it's not enough for me to upvote. For now, it'll be a novote.
							</div>

								
